noun.description: The period preceding a notable event.
examples: an acrimonious run-up to legislative elections

noun.description: An act of running briefly to gain momentum before performing a jump in track and field or other sports.
examples: high jumper Steve Smith will use his shortened five-stride run-up

noun.description: A low approach shot that bounces and runs forward.
An act of running an engine or turbine to prepare it for use or to test it.
A marked rise in the value or level of something.
examples: a sharp run-up of land and stock prices
